  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0ddd\u0db0 \u0db8\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dad\u0dcf \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dad\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Giant Maduwa entered the Guinness Book of Records",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The 13-foot-long 661-pound freshwater fish found in the Mekong River in Cambodia was listed in the Guinness Book of World Records as the world's largest fish yesterday (28).",
        "A group of fishermen on the Mikong River found the giant hut on June 13 in the Tsang Thrang province of northern Cambodia. At the time, it was making headlines around the world.",
        "The Guinness Book of World Records also noted that the pond was the largest freshwater fish in the world yesterday (28).",
        "The Cambodians named this giant shed 'Borami', which means 'full moon'. Zoologists have pointed out that 'Borami' is a rare freshwater shed."
      ],
